Launch the visual prompt editor with one command:

```bash
promptix studio
```

![Promptix Studio Dashboard](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Nisarg38/promptix-python/refs/heads/main/docs/images/promptix-studio-dashboard.png)

**Features:**
- ğŸ“Š **Dashboard** with prompt usage analytics
- ğŸ“š **Prompt Library** for browsing and editing
- ğŸ”„ **Version Management** with live/draft states
- âœï¸ **Visual Editor** with instant validation
- ğŸ“ˆ **Usage Statistics** for models and providers
- ğŸš€ **Quick Creation** of new prompts

---

## ğŸ—ï¸ Why Promptix?

### The Engineering Problem

In production LLM applications, your application logic is split between **code** and **prompts**. Both need professional engineering practices.

| Challenge | Without Promptix | With Promptix |
|-----------|------------------|---------------|
| ğŸ§ª **Testing Changes** | Hope for the best in production | Test draft versions in staging, promote when ready |
| ğŸ”§ **Updating Prompts** | Redeploy entire app for prompt tweaks | Update prompts independently, instant rollback |
| ğŸ **Code Organization** | Prompts scattered across files | Centralized, versioned prompt library |
| ğŸ­ **Dynamic Behavior** | Hardcoded if/else in strings | Context-aware templating with variables |
| ğŸ”„ **Multi-Provider** | Rewrite prompts for each API | One prompt, multiple providers |
| ğŸ‘¥ **Collaboration** | Edit strings in code PRs | Visual Studio UI for non-technical edits |
| ğŸ› **Debugging Issues** | Which version was live? | Full version history and diff |
| ğŸš€ **CI/CD Integration** | Manual prompt management | File-based, works with existing pipelines |

